===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|ls=ic|喬|室|abb1=yes}}.
Its exact structure changes depending on region and time period, but for most of its existence it has been a {{liushu|psc|nocap=yes}}. The phonetic has always been {{och-l|之}} or {{och-l|止}}.
: {{w|Oracle bone inscriptions}}: phonetic {{och-l|之}} + {{zh-l|*宀}}.
: {{w|Chu_(state)|Chu}} {{w|Bamboo_and_wooden_slips|slips}}: phonetic {{och-l|之}} + {{zh-l|*室}}
: {{w|Jin (Chinese state)|Jin}} slips: 
:* {{Han compound|ls=ic|喬|室|abb1=yes}}. This is the modern form inherited by {{w|Han dynasty|Han}} {{w|seal script}}.
:* Phonetic {{och-l|止}} + abbreviated  {{zh-l|*室}}
:* Phonetic {{och-l|之}} + {{zh-l|*室}}
: {{w|Qin}} dynasty: Phonetic {{och-l|止}} + {{zh-l|*高}} + {{zh-l|*室}}
{{w|Shuowen Jiezi}} interprets it as {{Han compound|ls=ic|之|高|室|abb2=yes|t1=foot|t2=high|t3=building|nocap=yes}} – a watch tower. The {{w|Shuowen Jiezi Zhu}} considers {{och-l|㞢}} (''*tjɯ'') to be the sound component.

